The paper discusses a new approach for software effort estimation using a mixture model that combines artificial neural network and fuzzy logic. This approach falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) as it deals with the estimation of software development effort. Additionally, the use of artificial neural network and fuzzy logic suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper also mentions the use of Neuro Fuzzy Inference System (NFIS) which is a type of neural network, indicating the relevance of neural networks (cs.NE) in the approach. Finally, the approach involves the integration of different components for better estimation, which suggests the involvement of systems and control (cs.SY) techniques.
